The _RMAppAttemptImpl_ creates an instance of ExpiredTransition which always sets the _finalAttemptState_ to FAILED.
{code}
private static final ExpiredTransition EXPIRED_TRANSITION =
      new ExpiredTransition();
. . .
    public ExpiredTransition() {
      super(RMAppAttemptState.FAILED);
    }
{code}
So, when my container successfully finishes regardless of the state (e.g., CONTAINER_FINISHED in my case), the _RMAppAttemptImpl.transition(..)_ does a switch on the _finalAttemptState_ and transitions to FAILED no matter what.
